# Agent Pipeline Protocol

Every subagent in the Olympus pipeline MUST follow this protocol to control their status in the visual overlay.

## How It Works

The pipeline state lives in `src/contexts/PipelineContext.tsx`. Agents control their status through a JSON file at `cursor/agents/pipeline-status.json`.

## Pipeline Status File

The file `cursor/agents/pipeline-status.json` is the single source of truth. When an agent starts working, Zeus (or the agent itself) writes to this file.

### Structure

```json
{
  "currentAgent": "hermes",
  "queue": ["athena", "apollo", "artemis", ...],
  "completed": {
    "hermes": { "startedAt": "ISO", "completedAt": "ISO", "elapsedMs": 5000, "summary": "..." }
  },
  "startedAt": "ISO"
}
```

## Agent Self-Declaration Protocol

When you (an agent) START working:
1. Read `cursor/agents/pipeline-status.json`
2. Set `currentAgent` to your agent ID
3. Remove yourself from `queue`
4. Write the file back

When you FINISH working:
1. Read `cursor/agents/pipeline-status.json`
2. Move yourself from `currentAgent` to `completed` with timing data
3. Set `currentAgent` to the next agent in `queue` (or null if empty)
4. Write the file back
5. Write your `status.json` to your output folder

